config BR2_PACKAGE_RTL8814AU_MORROWNR
	bool "rtl8814au-morrownr"
	depends on BR2_LINUX_KERNEL
	help
	  Out-of-tree Realtek RTL8814AU 4x4 802.11ac USB WiFi driver from
	  the morrownr fork (kernel-module package). RTL8814AU powers the
	  high-power 4-antenna adapters (Alfa AWUS1900, Netgear A7000,
	  etc.) and has NO mainline USB driver in 6.18 -- rtl8xxxu is
	  802.11n only, and neither rtw88 nor rtw89 cover it -- so an
	  out-of-tree driver is the only option. Same nl80211-only
	  CONFIG_WIRELESS_EXT analysis as the sibling morrownr packages
	  (see rtl8814au-morrownr.mk).

	  Sibling of package/rtl8812au and package/rtl8821au-morrownr: the
	  three morrownr forks together cover the 802.11ac Realtek USB chips
	  mainline still omits (RTL8812AU, RTL8811AU/RTL8821AU, RTL8814AU).

	  https://github.com/morrownr/8814au

comment "rtl8814au-morrownr needs a Linux kernel to be built"
	depends on !BR2_LINUX_KERNEL
